==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squamipen
<hw>Squam"i*pen</hw> <pr>(skw⟦acr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*p⟦ecr⟧n ⟦or⟧
skw⟦amac⟧"m⟦icr⟧-)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Squamipennes</plw> <pr>(-p⟦ecr⟧n"n⟦emac⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>squama</ets> a scale + <ets>penna</ets> a fin: cf. F.
<ets>squamipenne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of a
group of fishes having the dorsal and anal fins partially covered with
scales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They are compressed and mostly, bright-colored tropical
fishes, belonging to <gen>Chaetodon</gen> and allied genera. Many of
them are called <stype>coral fishes</stype>, and <stype>angel
fishes</stype>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squamoid</ent>⟦br⟧
